# Git & GitHub Workflow — Mandatory for the Agent

This rule defines **how the agent ships code** in this repo. It is the single source of truth for branching, commits, PRs, and merges. If anything below conflicts with another rule, **architectural rules win**, but the workflow here is otherwise non-negotiable.

> Repo: `KarmaCummunity/MVP-2` · Default branch: `main` · Merge strategy: **squash** · Auto-merge: **on, after CI passes**.

## 0. Pre-flight (verify once per session)

Before the first git operation in a session, confirm:

```bash
gh --version              # must succeed (GitHub CLI installed)
gh auth status            # must show "Logged in to github.com"
git config user.name      # must be non-empty
git config user.email     # must be non-empty
gh repo view --json nameWithOwner -q .nameWithOwner   # must be "KarmaCummunity/MVP-2"
```

If any check fails, **stop** and point the user to `SETUP_GIT_AGENT.md`. Do not improvise.

## 1. Decide the change class

Every change falls into exactly one of these classes:

| Class           | Trigger                                                        | Direct push to `main`? |
| --------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------- |
| **`hotfix-trivial`** | Typo in docs, comment, or string. **No code logic touched.**     | Allowed (with caution) |
| **`feature`**       | Anything tied to an `FR-*` or producing user-visible behavior.   | **Forbidden** — PR only |
| **`fix`**           | Bug fix that changes runtime behavior.                           | **Forbidden** — PR only |
| **`refactor`**      | Internal restructure, no behavior change.                        | **Forbidden** — PR only |
| **`chore`**         | Tooling, deps, CI, configs.                                      | **Forbidden** — PR only |
| **`docs`**          | Doc-only edit > a single line/typo (e.g. new section).           | **Forbidden** — PR only |

Direct push to `main` is allowed **only** for `hotfix-trivial`. When in doubt, open a PR.

## 2. Branch naming

`<type>/<FR-id-or-scope>-<kebab-short-desc>`

- `type` ∈ `feat | fix | refactor | chore | docs | test`
- Always include the `FR-*` ID if one exists; otherwise use a 1-2 word scope (`ci`, `deps`, `readme`).
- Keep the slug ≤ 50 chars.

Examples: `feat/FR-AUTH-001-otp-login`, `fix/FR-FEED-014-empty-state-crash`, `chore/ci-typecheck`, `docs/srs-glossary`.

## 3. Conventional Commits (English, mandatory)

Format: `<type>(<scope>)?: <subject>`

- **Type**: `feat | fix | refactor | chore | docs | test | perf | build | ci | style`.
- **Scope** (optional): package or area — `domain`, `mobile`, `infra`, `ui`, `srs`, `ci`.
- **Subject**: imperative mood, lowercase, no trailing period, ≤ 72 chars.
- **Body** (optional): wrap at 72; explain *why*, not *what*. Reference `FR-*` IDs.
- **Footer**: `BREAKING CHANGE: …` if applicable; closes issues with `Closes #N`.

Good: `feat(auth): add OTP verification screen for FR-AUTH-002`
Bad:  `update auth stuff`, `WIP`, `fixed bug`.

## 4. Pre-push gates (run from `app/`)

Before **every** `git push`, the agent runs and must see green:

```bash
cd app
pnpm typecheck
pnpm test
pnpm lint
```

If any fail: **do not push**. Either fix in a follow-up commit or revert and report. Never push red code.

## 5. Standard PR workflow

This is the canonical sequence. Follow it exactly for `feature | fix | refactor | chore | docs`.

```bash
# A. Sync main
git fetch origin
git switch main
git pull --ff-only origin main

# B. Create branch
git switch -c feat/FR-AUTH-001-otp-login

# C. Make atomic commits (each compiling, tests passing)
git add -p ; git commit -m "feat(auth): wire OTP repository port"
# … keep each commit small and self-contained

# D. Pre-push gates
( cd app && pnpm typecheck && pnpm test && pnpm lint )

# E. Push
git push -u origin HEAD

# F. Open PR
gh pr create \
  --base main \
  --head "$(git branch --show-current)" \
  --title "feat(auth): add OTP verification screen" \
  --body-file .github/.pr-body.md \
  --label "FR-AUTH" \
  --assignee "@me"

# G. Enable auto-merge (squash) — merges as soon as required checks pass
gh pr merge --auto --squash --delete-branch

# H. Wait for the merge, then sync local
gh pr checks --watch
git switch main
git pull --ff-only origin main
git branch -D feat/FR-AUTH-001-otp-login
```

Notes:
- The PR body file is generated by the agent on the fly (see §7).
- `--delete-branch` removes the remote branch on merge; the local delete in step H removes the local copy.
- If `gh pr merge --auto` errors with "auto-merge not enabled for repository", run the one-time fix in `SETUP_GIT_AGENT.md` §3.

## 6. The `hotfix-trivial` shortcut

For a *real* typo in docs/comments only:

```bash
git switch main && git pull --ff-only origin main
# edit
git commit -am "docs: fix typo in PROJECT_STATUS.md"
git push origin main
```

Never use this for code, configs, or anything users can see. If unsure → §5.

## 7. PR description template

Every PR body must include these sections (English). Generate the file at `.github/.pr-body.md` (gitignored) before calling `gh pr create`:

```markdown
## Summary
<2-4 sentences: what + why>

## Mapped to SRS
- FR-XXX-NNN — <title>  (link to `docs/SSOT/SRS/02_functional_requirements/<file>.md`)
- N/A for tooling/docs-only changes.

## Changes
- <bullet 1>
- <bullet 2>

## Tests
- `pnpm typecheck` — ✅
- `pnpm test`      — ✅ (X passed, Y skipped)
- `pnpm lint`      — ✅
- Manual: <what you clicked / what you saw>, or N/A.

## Refactor logged
Yes / No / NA — if Yes, link to `PROJECT_STATUS.md` §6 entry.

## Risk / rollout notes
<DB migrations? Feature flag? Breaking change? Otherwise: "Low risk — internal only.">

## Screenshots / logs
<only if UI or output changes>
```

## 8. Failure handling

| Symptom                                          | Action                                                                         |
| ------------------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| `git push` rejected (non-fast-forward)           | `git pull --rebase origin main`, resolve, re-run pre-push gates, push again.   |
| CI red on PR                                     | **Do not** force-merge. Push a follow-up commit fixing the failure.            |
| `gh pr merge --auto` fails with permission error | Stop. Report to user — likely needs `SETUP_GIT_AGENT.md` §3 or branch-protection adjustment. |
| Merge conflict during `gh pr merge`              | `git fetch origin && git rebase origin/main`, resolve, re-run gates, push.    |
| Stale `.git/index.lock`                          | Verify no other git process is running, then `rm .git/index.lock`. Note in PR. |
| Unintended files staged (`.DS_Store`, secrets)   | `git restore --staged <file>`, add to `.gitignore`, never commit secrets.      |

## 9. Hard prohibitions (never, even on user request)

- **Never** force-push to `main` (`git push --force` to `main` is forbidden).
- **Never** rewrite published history on a shared branch (`git rebase -i` on a pushed branch).
- **Never** commit secrets (`.env`, API keys, tokens). If detected: stop, surface to user, do not push.
- **Never** merge a PR with red required checks.
- **Never** open a PR without a `Mapped to SRS` line.
- **Never** delete a branch you didn't create unless the user asked.

## 10. Wiring with the SSOT rules

Every PR that ships an `FR-*` change must, in the **same** PR:

1. Update `docs/SSOT/PROJECT_STATUS.md` per `project-status-tracking.mdc`.
2. Honor architecture invariants per `srs-architecture.mdc` (file size cap, layer boundaries, error types).
3. Begin every code-bearing response with the verification gate:
   ```
   Mapped to SRS: [Requirement ID]. Refactor logged: [Yes/No/NA].
   ```

A PR that touches a feature without updating `PROJECT_STATUS.md` is incomplete and must not be auto-merged.

## 11. Quick reference card

```
sync       : git fetch && git switch main && git pull --ff-only
branch     : git switch -c <type>/<FR-id>-<slug>
gate       : ( cd app && pnpm typecheck && pnpm test && pnpm lint )
push       : git push -u origin HEAD
PR         : gh pr create --base main --title "<conv-commit>" --body-file .github/.pr-body.md
auto-merge : gh pr merge --auto --squash --delete-branch
wait       : gh pr checks --watch
cleanup    : git switch main && git pull --ff-only && git branch -D <branch>
```
